### Warning (Warning)

# ====================== ♥ Warning ======================

The purpose of the script is to install the necessary software (packages) and launch the necessary services.
The point is that you make all the changes beforehand in the script itself and get the opportunity to quickly install the utilities (packages) that You have decided to install (provided That you have changed it for yourself, otherwise the script will install the software (packages) prescribed initially.
While the script is running) You will be asked questions about installing a particular utility (package) - be careful! Installed software (packages), fonts - downloaded and installed from the 'Official arch Linux repositories'. There is also software (packages), fonts - installed from the user repository 'AUR'-'yay', are collected and installed. If you doubt your actions, you can use the script as a cheat sheet by opening it in a text editor, copying commands to install the necessary packages, and launch the necessary services. In any situation, the choice is always yours. You either walk in the rain, or just get wet under it.${RED}

